                                NoFastMem

        Some very old program may not run properly when memory other than
graphics memory is present in the Amiga system. In this case,
double-clicking on the NoFastMem icon forces the Amiga to use only the
available graphics memory. The icon works like a toggle switch. To restore
all memory to the system, double-click on the NoFastMem icon again.


